mpliance-assistant` simulation. It includes detailed actions like payload inspection, PII scanning, and redaction with a zero-trust gateway. Human approval involves a DPO review and whitelisting. The system outputs gateway session details, compliance status, and action taken, now ready to visualize.\n\n\n**Defining Customer Experience**\n\nI'm now detailing the `customer-experience` agent simulation. I must represent a VIP client's frustration with delayed delivery of a server rack. I'm focusing on the agent's interpretation, the knowledge needed, and the actions it should take. The system includes Emotional Sentiment Detection, Contextual CRM Search, and resolution strategy. I also have a human approval point for very high-priority VIP clients.\n\n\n**Simulating Operations Actions**\n\nI'm now detailing the `operations-copilot` simulation. The challenge focuses on predicting turbine failure. This agent interprets sensor data, identifies wear metrics, and gathers logs. I'm focusing on actions like telemetry pulls, anomaly synthesis, manual retrieval, and dispatch pre-authorization. A Plant Director's manual sign-off on the order is required.\n\n\n**Refining Operational Details**\n\nI'm now detailing the simulated actions for the `operations-copilot` agent. I've included telemetry pulls, anomaly synthesis, and manual retrieval, with pre-authorization for dispatch. The system includes a compliance check for safety certifications and generates an output with an asset ID, anomaly rating, wear indicator, maintenance recommendation, and required parts. I'm verifying the inclusion of these properties will not break any existing code.\n\n\n**Integrating Static Simulation**\n\nI'm now thinking about how to integrate all these concepts into the UI. I will show a static warning and a dynamic step-by-step display. I'm focusing on making a clear and engaging simulation. I am also planning to rename or add a new simulation tab to the UI.\n\n\n**Visualizing Simulated Workflow**\n\